Lionel Messi was banned for four international matches - just five and a half hours before Argentina's World Cup qualifier against Bolivia kicked off.The Barcelona forward was punished for directing "insulting words" at an assistant referee during Thursday's 1-0 win over Chile.Messi, who scored the only goal in the qualifier, was angered when he was penalised for a foul, waving and shouting at the assistant in response.The 29-year-old was fined Â£8,100.